d":"Largs, Ayrshire, Scotland","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Churchman","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: from Middle English <i>chirch(e)man</i> ‘clergyman; churchwarden; lay official responsible for church finances’. The earliest examples would have denoted a custodian or keeper of a church (Old English <i>cyriceman</i>), not a clergyman, though the earlier sense had probably been superseded by the time the surname arose.","Possibly an Americanized form (translation into English) of German <b>Kirchmann</b> (see   Kirchman  )."],"variants":[{"name":"Kirchman","meanings":["Americanized form of German   Kirchmann  ."]}]},{"name":"Alice","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Originally a variant of   Adelaide  , representing an Old French spelling of a reduced form of Germanic <i>Adalheidis</i>. <i>Alice</i> and <i>Adelaide</i> were already regarded as distinct names in English during the medieval period. <i>Alice</i> enjoyed a surge of popularity in the 19th century and periods of favour ever since. It was the name of the central character of  Lewis Carroll's  Alice's Adventures in Wonderland (  1865 ) and Through the Looking Glass (  1872 ), who was based on his child friend  Alice Liddell , daughter of the Dean of Christ Church, Oxford."],"variants":[{"name":"Alys","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Alice ."]},{"name":"Alis","meanings":["equivalent of <b>Alice</b> ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Alice L Churchman was born in 1430, in Largs, Ayrshire, Scotland. She had at least 1 son and 1 daughter with Sir John Shaa III. She died in 1475, in Scotland, at the age of 45."},"et":{"1430–1475":"1430–1475","1425–1471":"1425–1471","1455–1503":"1455–1503","1464–1528":"1464–1528","1503":"1503","1425":"1425","1455":"1455","1464":"1464","1475":"1475","1430":"1430","24 May 1471":"24. mai 1471","1471":"1471","1528":"1528","Scotl